The paper focuses on deep learning systems for image segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed Semantic Bottleneck Networks (SBN) aim to improve interpretability of deep learning systems, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of semantic concepts and materials, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of high-level reasoning to analyze failure cases and modes, which is relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
